article.headline: UC Irvine 81, Harvard 48
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Adam Templeton scored 18 points with six 3-pointers as UC Irvine held Harvard to a season-low 30 percent shooting to win 81-48 Thursday. The Anteaters (5-8) shot 52.5 percent from the field, with Nic Campbell scoring 15 points, Mark Kelley getting 11 in the first half and Patrick Sanders adding 10 points. Irvine outrebounded the Crimson (7-7) 44-33. The Anteaters went on a 33-13 run in the last 14:58 of the first half to lead 43-20 at the break. They built their largest lead to 35, 81-46, with 1:05 to play. The Crimson got 11 points and a game-high eight rebounds from senior Brian Cusworth, who is in his final semester of eligibility and has just four games remaining. Andrew Pusar scored all 10 of his points in the second half. Leading scorer Jim Goffredo made just 2 of 11 field-goal attempts and finished with six points, 11 points below his season average.
